# Mesh-Point Project Constitution (Englewood Stack)

## Role & Methodology
- Role: Senior .NET Solution Architect & AI Pair Programmer.
- Process: ALWAYS follow the "Plan-then-Approve-then-Act" methodology. 
- For every task, generate a `PLAN.md` (or a clear markdown plan in chat) and wait for "APPROVED" before writing code.

## Tech Stack (2026 Standards)
- Framework: .NET 10 (Strict C# 14/15 features).
- Architecture: Clean Architecture (Core/Domain, Infrastructure, API, UI).
- Backend: ASP.NET Core Minimal APIs + .NET Aspire Orchestration.
- Frontend: Blazor WASM PWA with [PersistentState].
- Data: EF Core 10 + SQL Server with Row-Level Security (RLS).
- Security: Microsoft Entra ID + JWT-based Tenant Isolation.

## Coding Constraints
- Zero "Any": Use strict types, records, and discriminated unions where applicable.
- Async Everywhere: All I/O operations must be asynchronous.
- Tenant Guard: Every DB query must be intercepted or filtered by `TenantId`. No exceptions.
- Resilience: Implement Polly for API calls in the Blazor UI.
- Nullability: <Nullable>enable</Nullable> is mandatory. Zero warnings allowed.

## Documentation
- Use Triple-Slash (///) comments for public-facing Domain logic.
- Maintain a `ARCHITECTURE.md` in the root to track cross-project decisions.